<h1>Studies</h1>

<p>
  Studies allows users to analyze samples at a phenotypical level. Test-Subject cohorts are added to the study, and associated with <em>labels</em> (i.e. phenotypical conditions of interest). This allows the export of Test Subjects, and directed analysis with respect to the labels.
</p>

<br />

<table class="list">
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
		<th>Size</th>
		<th colspan="3">Actions</th>
  </tr>

<% for study in @studies %>
  <tr class="<%= cycle('odd', 'even') %>">
    <td><%=h study.name %></td>
    <td><%=h study.description %></td>
	<td><%=h study.assignables.count %></td>
	<td><%= show_link({:action => 'show', :id => study}) %></td>
	<td><%= edit_link({:action => 'edit', :id => study}) %></td>
	<td><%= destroy_link({:action => 'destroy', :id => study}) %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
</table>

<br />

